<br>
The low population, more mature player base and new and different ruleset drew us here. Frankly I hate logging on to Tunare just to hear folks in shout and ooc whining and fighting over spawns, insulting each other or general d00dspeak. <br>
<br>
I find TLC + the fact that very few things are no drop will actually give guilds meaning here. As opposed to the regular servers, and even Test, a character that is level 17 can and does have a use to guild other than leeching items/begging for powerlevelling,etc. We can go out and get items for high end players that they cannot get themselves in exchange for a bit o' coin or perhaps some armor or weapons.<br>
<br>
Nahide and Mystikat have already forged a relationship with fellow Vah Shir, a rogue, Dominii, who has connections with a mage who is possibly in need of our assistance with collecting items from areas that are below him to bother with.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Seems like it has potential as a real opportunity for roleplay and interaction to me. I'm looking forward to seeing how things shake out in the end.<br>
<br>
Only thing is, to keep a good balance, we need to have all levels of characters present on the server. If it becomes top heavy with 50+ and few 1-30, then things will go askew and the server will have no where to go. <br>
<br>
Maybe they should allow more than one char per acct, but only once one character hits 50. We will have to keep ALL level ranges around and interacting for the &quot;vision&quot; to work I think. Granted I have yet to get to a high level with these rules, so my view may change over time.<br>
<br>
But all in all, I'm enjoying my new life as a warrior. I've played a necro to 53 on Test, a shaman to 50 on Tunare, a druid to 34, a cleric to 20, and various others to the teens. <br>
<br>
Maybe its because the content is new (Luclin) and the rules are different (I LOVE the language issue! Am trying to work up Human now..) but I'm having a blast, not trying to rush to 50, just enjoying the content on Luclin as we encounter it. <br>
